Git 2/5    (terminology)

Repository =  a git project ( has a .git directory)

Commit = snapshot in time of the whole file with changes made ( new state ) 

Branch = a point to a specific commit to show where we are working 

Origin / Remote = reference to an external host where the project lives ( Github ) 

Staging Area / index = the buffer between working directory ( local files edited ) -> staging (buffer) -> Main branch/repo 

.git/index = a binary folder that holds the staging area info 

Blobs = ( binary large object ) stores the actual content of the files - just raw data

Trees = folder that show which files and directories are inside 

Head = pointer to shower where you are currently working in the repo 

Object store = storage area for where blobs , trees and commits are held 

Tag = label you put on commit to mark special version or release. 


Git workflow:

1. Developer pulls main branch / clones repo with latest code 
2. Create a feature branch 
3. Work locally -> make commits -> push to local repo 
4. Open pull request on github and is reviewed and merged in 
5. Team syncs regularly with  

